judge joseph f anderson of federal district court in columbia ended eight years of federal oversight of the state department of juvenile justice that began as a result of a lawsuit against the department in 1990 the suit said juveniles in state prisons suffered overcrowding and abuse and poor health care food and education since the federal government began oversight in 1995 the department has built new wilderness camps for nonviolent offenders focused on education and job skills started sports leagues and hired more guards partly thanks to 7 million in new financing from the legislature this year said the department 's director bill byars ariel hart nyt

